cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of deep reinforcement learning-based navigation systems to adversarial attacks, which falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the potential risks of intentionally adaptive attacks, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses open-source robot learning and navigation control environments, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
